<br>
&quot;I know of at least 1 person who was sent a tell asking if they wiped yet.&quot; -- Would that still amount to &quot;breathing down their necks&quot; if those tells were sent from another zone?  At least this person you speak of wasn't so stupid to make an issue out of it, like you have just done.  And once again, I'll remind you that our two guilds were as far apart from eachother as two guilds can be in that zone.  They were done with aten by the time we were barely through TVK's room.<br>
<br>
&quot;Who cares if they leave shit up&quot; -- I care.  When spawns are spread out the zone is not worth raiding.  When warders are fucked up it forces you to deal with the GMs to raid at all.  I care about raid zones that can and should be worth raiding but are not viable targets due to others' poor performance which happens to be allowed due only to unearned advantage.<br>
<br>
&quot;If they want to leave something up, then so be it.&quot; -- Um, I'll give a big Fuck No to that one.  If they leave stuff up then others are damn well entitled to go in, just like we did.  How long should we wait?  What if one of them fell asleep at the keyboard in atens room, how long before we can start breathing down their necks to kill mobs they passed up hours ago and aren't going back for?  What if all 33 of them do?<br>
<br>
&quot;But to go in before is just a bad judgement call.&quot; -- Obviously our judgements of the situation differ.  Given that you weren't there and I was, and that you're only still talking because you are trying to gracefully step down from the stupid position you put yourself into in this thread, I think i'll go with my judgement if that's A-OK with you.<br>
<br>
&quot;you guys had no reason to be there other than to &quot;hope&quot;&quot; -- I already told you, NOBODY FAILS to aten, not even ToS.  The encounter was obviously designed to be un-losable to anyone who can fight through the other mobs. <br>
<br>
&quot;They win don't they&quot; -- I didnt say they didnt win.  Didn't I say multiple times already that they succeeded?  So what are you rambling on about here?<br>
<br>
<br>
Bygzalf says, &quot;'The War Councils Might Makes Right' rules of engagement&quot; -- No I already explained, our rules of engagement are known as First In Force.  That was like the 3rd sentence in my previous post.  I think Might Makes Right is our philosphy, or our charter, or maybe its just roleplaying bullshit--definitely not our rules of engagement though, I can personally assure you of that since I do in fact define our policy.<br>
<br>
&quot;Maybe if you treated guilds that arent to your level yet with more respect, the guilds that you are lagging behind would treat you with more respect.&quot; -- First, I see no connection between your hypothesis and your conclusion.  Second, I don't see what disrespect has taken place.  In fact, contrary to the idea that we treat nobody with respect, the policies I outline above state exactly how and when respect is given out, and we follow them pretty evenly.  The only thing that wasnt given to GoL/Fam by TWC in this incident was pure charity.  <br>
